    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{3yt-y^{2}t^{2}}{y^{2}t^{2}+2yt-15}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{yt}{yt+5}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common terms:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{3yt-y^{2}t^{2}}{y^{2}t^{2}+2yt-15}} \amp = \frac{{yt\mathopen{}\left(3-yt\right)}}{{\left(yt-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(yt+5\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{-yt\mathopen{}\left(yt-3\right)}}{{\left(yt-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(yt+5\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{yt}{yt+5}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
